    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#robinson1913"/>, p. 164, n. <citedRange>17</citedRange> (without illustration)</bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#Sammelbuch"/> <citedRange>5875</citedRange></bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#DGE"/> <citedRange>231,1</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>009500</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63076"><name nymRef="#Ἀριστέας">Ἀριστέας</name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63044"><name nymRef="#Ἀρίμναστος" type="patronymic">Ἀριμνάστō</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Aristeas fils d'Arimnastos.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Aristeas son of Arimnastos.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Aristeas figlio di Arimnastos.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>أريستيس بن أريمناستوس.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Width 1.35 is given by Robinson, from De Cou's notes. It seems improbable, such grave steles being rather ca. 0.55 broad. It should be an error for height.</p>
                <p>From the copy in block-letters, it is difficult to judge of the date. If the last letter is really an omicron, the inscription could still belong to the end of V BC.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
